<h1 id="problem-honey-bunches-of-oats">Problem: Honey Bunches of Oats</h1>
<ul>
<li><p>(Sipser 5.3) Find a match in the following instance of the Post Correspondence Problem:</p>
<p><span class="math display">\[
  \left\{ \tile{ab}{abab}, \tile{b}{a}, \tile{aba}{b}, \tile{aa}{a} \right\}.
\]</span></p></li>
<li><p>(Sipser 5.17) Show that the PCP problem is <em>decidable</em> over the unary alphabet <span class="math inline">\(\Sigma = \{\, a \,\}\)</span>.</p>
<p>(<em>Hint</em>: With one symbol, you can safely consider the <em>number</em> of symbols on the top and bottom of each tile. From there, think about fractionsâ€¦)</p></li>
</ul>
